def: Evils; wrongs; offenses against right and law. Mala in se Etym:[L.] (Law), offenses which are such from their own nature, at commonlaw, irrespective of statute.-- Mala prohibita Etym: [L.] (Law), offenses prohibited by statute,as distinguished from mala in se, which are offenses at common law.
To graft by cutting the scion and stock in a certain manner.See Whip grafting, under Grafting.
To disappear gradually in another surface, as where moldingsare lost in a sloped or curved face.
A rubbing or grinding; trituration. [Obs.] Cheyne.
Successor or vicar; -- a title of the successors of Mohammedboth as temporal and spiritual rulers, now used by the sultans ofTurkey, [Writting also calif.]
A female arbiter; an arbitratrix. Milton.
Low in style, and irregular in measure; as, doggerel rhymes.This may well be rhyme doggerel, quod he. Chaucer.
One versed in pantology; a writer of pantology.
A red variety of zircon, sometimes used as a gem. See Zircon.Hyacinth bean (Bot.), a climbing leguminous plant (Dolichos Lablab),related to the true bean. It has dark purple flowers and fruit.
Pertaining to a second canon, or ecclesiastical writing ofinferior authority; -- said of the Apocrypha, certain Epistles, etc.
